{"word":"χεῖμα","slug":"χεῖμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χεῖμα</b></el> <el>(χεῖμα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:χιών'><el>χιών</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>winter-weather, cold, frost</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>hiems</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>winter</i> as a season of the year, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>θέρος</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, attic; <el>χεῖμα</el> (<a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>) <i>in winter</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; so <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <el>χείματι</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a storm</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}